:"1070","1137":"1137","1103":"1103","1078":"1078","29 April 1042":"29 April 1042","1109":"1109","1119":"1119","Arras, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","Arras, Pas-De-Calais, Nord-Pas-De-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Arras, Dibër, Albania":"Arras, Dibër, Albania","nameMeanings":[{"name":"D'Arras","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Norman or Huguenot origin) or French: habitational name, with fused preposition <i>d(e)</i>, principally for someone from Arras in northern France, or possibly from Arras-en-Lavedan (Hautes-Pyrénées) or Arras-sur-Rhône (Ardèche). The name was first brought to Britain by the Normans, and from the 16th century reintroduced by Protestant refugees from France."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Jean","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Like   Jane   and   Joan  , a medieval variant of Old French <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Towards the end of the Middle Ages this form became largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]},{"name":"Borel","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Anglo-Norman: Bokel, a buckle"],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Chevalier croisé Jean Borel D'Arras was born about 1040, in Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France as the son of Elgot I D'Arras. He married Thamar de Marcatel in 1060, in Mercatel, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France. He died in 1119, in Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 80."},"et":{"about 1040–1119":"umbes 1040–1119","1040–1119":"1040–1119","1054–1109":"1054–1109","1040–Female":"1040–Surnud","1070–1103":"1070–1103","1078–1137":"1078–1137","1010–1042":"1010–1042","about 1040":"umbes 1040","1077":"1077","1010":"1010","1054":"1054","1042":"1042","1040":"1040","1071":"1071","1070":"1070","1137":"1137","1103":"1103","1078":"1078","29 April 1042":"29. aprill 1042","1109":"1109","1119":"1119","Arras, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Arras, Pas-De-Calais, Nord-Pas-De-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Arras, Dibër, Albania":"Arras, Dibër, Albaania"},"fi":{"about 1040–1119":"noin 1040–1119","1040–1119":"1040–1119","1054–1109":"1054–1109","1040–Female":"1040–Kuollut","1070–1103":"1070–1103","1078–1137":"1078–1137","1010–1042":"1010–1042","about 1040":"noin 1040","1077":"1077","1010":"1010","1054":"1054","1042":"1042","1040":"1040","1071":"1071","1070":"1070","1137":"1137","1103":"1103","1078":"1078","29 April 1042":"29. huhtikuuta 1042","1109":"1109","1119":"1119","Arras, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","Arras, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Arras, 